+  <!-- Operation cards -->
+  <text x="72" y="664" class="section">Computational meaning of the optical paths</text>
+  <rect x="72" y="690" width="356" height="244" fill="#fbfdff" stroke="#1f5fd1" stroke-width="2"/>
+  <text x="96" y="725" class="card-title" fill="#1f5fd1">01  Prepare a protected physical qubit</text>
+  <text x="96" y="757" class="body">1S0 → 3P0 through the 3D1 pumping path</text>
+  <text x="96" y="782" class="small">Local 556 nm + global 1539 nm pump into</text>
+  <text x="96" y="802" class="small">the metastable nuclear-spin manifold. This</text>
+  <text x="96" y="822" class="small">creates the storage basis; it is not a gate.</text>
+  <text x="96" y="875" class="small" fill="#53615d">Li et al. (2025): 3D1 pumping during trap-off windows.</text>
+
+  <rect x="448" y="690" width="356" height="244" fill="#fbfefc" stroke="#187a44" stroke-width="2"/>
+  <text x="472" y="725" class="card-title" fill="#187a44">02  Apply single-qubit rotations</text>
+  <text x="472" y="757" class="body">RF: |0&gt; ↔ |1&gt; within 3P0</text>
+  <text x="472" y="782" class="small">An RF drive supplies the directly usable</text>
+  <text x="472" y="802" class="small">one-qubit primitive Rφ(θ). Site selectivity</text>
+  <text x="472" y="822" class="small">requires a resolved frequency or local light shift.</text>
+  <text x="472" y="875" class="small" fill="#53615d">Ma et al. (2022): nuclear-spin gate operations.</text>
+
+  <rect x="824" y="690" width="356" height="244" fill="#fcfbff" stroke="#6542b5" stroke-width="2"/>
+  <text x="848" y="725" class="card-title" fill="#6542b5">03  Create an entangling gate</text>
+  <text x="848" y="757" class="body">302 nm: |1&gt; ↔ |r&gt;</text>
+  <text x="848" y="782" class="small">State-selective Rydberg excitation makes a</text>
+  <text x="848" y="802" class="small">two-atom interaction conditional. A calibrated</text>
+  <text x="848" y="822" class="small">blockade sequence returns a controlled phase to 3P0.</text>
+  <text x="848" y="875" class="small" fill="#53615d">Ma et al. (2023): metastable-qubit Rydberg CZ path.</text>
+
+  <rect x="1200" y="690" width="328" height="244" fill="#fffdfb" stroke="#e05c26" stroke-width="2"/>
+  <text x="1224" y="725" class="card-title" fill="#e05c26">04  Measure and classify</text>
+  <text x="1224" y="757" class="body">Raman map → 497 depump → image</text>
+  <text x="1224" y="782" class="small">Map |0&gt;, then |1&gt;, to 3P2; return each</text>
+  <text x="1224" y="802" class="small">mapped state to 1S0, then acquire two images:</text>
+  <text x="1224" y="822" class="small">bright/dark, dark/bright, or dark/dark.</text>
+  <text x="1224" y="875" class="small" fill="#53615d">Li et al. (2025): loss-resolved spin record.</text>
+
+  <rect x="72" y="962" width="1456" height="218" fill="#f5f8f6" stroke="#cbd5d0"/>
+  <text x="96" y="998" class="section">Decoder-visible consequence</text>
+  <text x="96" y="1030" class="body">RF rotates the nuclear-spin qubit. The Rydberg path supplies a conditional two-qubit phase.</text>
+  <text x="96" y="1054" class="body">Raman mapping plus imaging produces a ternary measurement record: |0&gt;, |1&gt;, or loss.</text>
+  <text x="96" y="1078" class="body">The 369 nm branch converts a Rydberg error into an ionization event that can be reported as an erasure.</text>
+  <line x1="96" y1="1100" x2="1504" y2="1100" class="guide"/>
+  <text x="96" y="1130" class="small" fill="#53615d">Sources represented in this teaching map: Ma et al., PRX 12, 021028 (2022); Ma et al., PRX Quantum 4, 020327 (2023); Li et al., arXiv:2504.11995 (2025). Wavelengths and pulse programs are implementation-dependent.</text>
+  <text x="96" y="1156" class="small" fill="#53615d">399 nm is a ground-state fluorescence channel. It does not directly discriminate a qubit stored in 3P0; state-selective mapping is required first.</text>
